com.gotenna.sdk.data

Class GTError

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gotenna.sdk.data.GTError

  • public final class GTError
extends java.lang.Object
    Represent a goTenna Error that should be handled.

    Created on 4/8/15.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int COMMAND_TIME_OUT_ERROR_CODE
      Error code to indicate when we send a command to the goTenna but do not get a response back after waiting a certain amount of time.
      static int DATA_LENGTH_EXCEEDS_LIMITS_CODE
      Error code to indicate when the amount of data sent with a single message exceeds the limits imposed by the SDK.
      static int DATA_RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
      Error code to indicate when data rate limit for the amount of data sent with the goTenna has been temporarily exceeded.
      static int FAILED_TO_PROCESS_COMMAND_CODE
      Error code to indicate when a command that was sent is not processed by the goTenna successfully, such as when the command was sent but a response for it was not receive from the goTenna.
      static int GOTENNA_BUSY_CODE
      Error code to indicate that the goTenna is too busy to process this command right now.
      static int GROUP_SECRET_NOT_FOUND_CODE
      Error code to indicate when a group message is sent, but the group secret used to encrypt the message could not be found.
      static int HAS_NOT_SETUP_GOTENNA_CODE
      Error code to indicate when a valid goTenna user has not been setup via the UserDataStore class.
      static int INVALID_APP_TOKEN_CODE
      Error code to indicate when the supplied application token is invalid.
      static int INVALID_DATA_ERROR
      Error code to indicate when we got invalid data inside a command response.
      static int NACK_ERROR
      Error code to indicate when we got a nack but could not report it through the usual channels.
      static int NOT_SUPER_SDK_USER
      Error code to indicate when the sdk developer is not allowed to use a specific function because they do not have a super sdk token.
      static int RESERVED_GID_CODE
      Error code to indicate that a GID you are trying to use is reserved for other purposes.
      static int USER_GID_CODE
      Error code to indicate that a GID you are trying to use is the user's GID.
